text:
Functioning similarly to Fire Emblem Engage, heavy weapons always attack second and can't double the enemy by regular means. Here they're also effective against frozen enemies.
These weapons will shove the attacked unit.{br}
Additionally, in particular: Blade attacks will Cleave when initiating.{br}Greatlances gain +2 Range on Enemy Phase.{br}And Warhammer attacks inflict Flinch on enemies within 2 tiles of target.

In this game, there are two kinds of staves:{br}
Support staves can only be used by support classes. Support classes have a staff icon <icon>Staff</> in their description.{br}
Offensive staves can be used to attack and don't have the support class restriction. Some of these staves will always hit, giving staff users a safer attack option, but they can't crit.

Slim weapons of every kind can be found in the ch2 shop and grant extra WEXP.{br}
Fire weapons (of any kind) are effective against Horse units.{br}
Thunder weapons (of any kind) are effective against Armor units.{br}
Wind weapons (of any kind) are effective against Flying units.{br}
Light magic is usually 3 range.
Light magic and daggers will do extra damage when doing a critical hit. This means that even if a normal hit would do 0 damage, you'll damage the enemy with a critical hit.

The weapon triangle's effects can be higher than in the original games.{br}
They can affect your critical hit rate against enemies.{br}
Bows are part of the weapon triangle and have an advantage against magic.{br}
Swords and Light vs Axe and Dark: +4 DMG, -2 DMG taken, +10 Hit, +20 Avoid, +5 Crit, +5 Dodge.{br}
Axe and Dark vs Lances and Anima: + 6 DMG, -2 DMG taken, +20 Hit, +20 Avoid, +3 AS.{br}
Lances and Anima vs Swords and Light: +2 DMG, -4 DMG taken, +5 Hit, +10 Avoid, +20 Dodge.{br}
Bows vs All Tomes/Staves: +15 DMG, -10 DMG taken, +30 Hit, +10 Avoid, +8 Crit.

Growth rates are now visible in your unit's info. Your units' growths can change in several ways:{br}
Promoting: Now, besides gaining stats, your units get bonus growths upon promoting, sometimes drastically altering the unit's statline.
Conversations: some base convos can improve an unit's growths.
Held items: items that used to be stats boosters or promotion items are now held items that among their effects, typically improve a unit's growth rates. Metis Tome's effects have been improved.{br}
All of your units have Con and Mov growths, so they have a chance to level up those stats.

Supports are now easier to obtain, and more similar to how it works in Awakening.
The limit of supports is that you can only have one A support. You can have all the B supports you want.
If you obtained enough points in the previous map to trigger a conversation you can activate it from the base too.
The range for getting support points is now is 2 spaces{br}There are more ways to gain support points besides ending turn near each other:
By interacting (using staves or dancing).{br}By battling on range of the partner.{br}By battling on pair up with a partner.
Support bonuses have been buffed to compensate the increased enemy power.{br}
Fire (C/B/A): +3/6/12 DMG, +5/10/20 Hit, +5/10/20 Avoid, +2/4/6 Crit, +3/6/12 Defense Speed.{br}
Wind (C/B/A): +3/6/12 DMG, +5/10/20 Hit, +2/4/6 Crit, +5/10/20 Dodge, +3/6/12 Attack Speed.{br}
Thunder (C/B/A): -3/6/12 DMG taken, +5/10/20 Avoid, +2/4/6 Crit, +5/10/20 Dodge, +3/6/12 Attack Speed.{br}
Ice (C/B/A): -3/6/12 DMG taken, +5/10/20 Hit, +5/10/20 Avoid, +5/10/20 Dodge, +3/6/12 Defense Speed.{br}
Dark (C/B/A): +3/6/12 DMG, +5/10/20 Hit, +5/10/20 Avoid, +2/4/6 Crit, +5/10/20 Dodge.{br}
Light (C/B/A): +3/6/12 DMG, -3/6/12 DMG taken, +5/10/20 Hit, +5/10/20 Avoid, +2/4/6 Crit.{br}
Anima (C/B/A): +3/6/12 DMG, -3/6/12 DMG taken, +5/10/20 Hit, +5/10/20 Avoid, +5/10/20 Dodge.
